1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 29-22 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to juror counseling.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 29-22 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Juror counseling following graphic evidence or testimony.
7 1. The court shall offer, not more than ten hours of post-trial psychological counseling,
8 without charge, to a juror or alternate juror who served on a trial jury in a trial involving
9 extraordinarily graphic, gruesome, or emotional evidence or testimony.
10 2. The counseling offered under subsection 1 applies only to a juror or alternate juror
11 who served on a trial jury for a trial involving the following offenses:
12 a. Murder under section 12.1 - 16 - 01 ;
13 b. Manslaughter under section 12.1 - 16 - 02 ;
14 c. Negligent homicide under section 12.1 - 16 - 03 ;
15 d. Felony-level assault or domestic violence under chapter 12.1 - 17 ;
16 e. A sexual offense under chapter 12.1 - 20 or 12.1 - 27.2 ;
17 f. Abuse or neglect of a child under sections 14 - 09 - 22 and 14 - 09 - 22.1; and
18 g. Others as determined by the court.
19 3. The counseling offered under this section:
20 a. Must occur not later than one hundred eighty days after the jury is discharged;
21 b. May be provided by the court system, by a state agency, or by contract; and
22 c. May be individual or group counseling.
